issue.title: Support different input types

labels.name: feature request
labels.description: request for unsupported feature or enhancement

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**
In order to use the inference session I need to use `ReadOnlySpan` for inputs, but it seems [this type](
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/51942986/types-with-embedded-references-are-not-supported) is not supported in VS2015. We just need to pass an array of float but Tensors rely on Span.

**System information**
- ONNX Runtime version (you are using): 0.3.0

**Describe the solution you'd like**
Support Visual Studio 2015 
1. alternative to Tensor as input
2. accept float[] directly with a dimensions
3. accept Bitmap (to avoid one extra marshaling) (add utility to convert Bitmap to Tensor?)

**Describe alternatives you've considered**

```c#
var t = System.Numerics.Tensors.ArrayTensorExtensions.ToTensor(array).Reshape(new[] { 1, 3, image.Height, image.Width})
```

**Additional context**
Our current code is based on VS2015
More [information](https://devblogs.microsoft.com/dotnet/welcome-to-c-7-2-and-span/). 
[This issue](https://github.com/Microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/540) is related
